title: 'SNL': Beyoncé goes for an ultrasound to check on the twins
text:
'SNL': Beyoncé goes for an ultrasound to check on the twins Jayme Deerwester , USA TODAY Published 1:10 a.m. ET Feb. 12, 2017 | Updated 3 minutes ago 
Bey and Jay, you should hear what those babies are saying about you. (Photo: JUSTIN LANE, EPA) 
Is there a better place to be right now than Beyoncé's uterus? 
Saturday Night Live doesn't think so, so they sent Bey (Sasheer Zamata) to the OB-GYN for an ultrasound to see what's going on in there. 
Lo and behold, the babies look an awful lot like Tracy Morgan and Kenan Thompson in T-shirts, diapers and rubber tubing for umbilical cords. 
"I just feel like we're different than other babies," Baby Tracy noted. 
"Yeah, we different," Baby Kenan confirmed. "You know who our mama is?" 
"I don't know, but I think she's important," Tracy mused. "When people meet her, they scream, so she's either a beautiful queen or a goblin." 
"Yo, our mama is Beyoncé, man," Kenan explained to his brother, who was drawing a blank. 
"Wow, I haven't even breathed yet, and I know who Beyoncé is!" Life is good for Beyoncé's twins. #SNL pic.twitter.com/71At22mXRW — Saturday Night Live (@nbcsnl) February 12, 2017 
Back out in the exam room, her doctor (Alec Baldwin) hazarded a guess: "It may be too early to say, but I think these babies came to slay." 
They threw so much shade it made it hard to see anything on the ultrasound. 
When Baby Kenan said he was trying to not to bother their mother, who was having a hard enough time carrying them, Tracy wasn't having it. 
"Oh no, she's not," he countered. "I heard she carried two full-grown ladies for 10 years named Michelle and Kelly!" Read or Share this story: http://usat.ly/2l2t8JI Most Popular
